    en: "New York Personal Property Law Article 10 (Personal Property Law § 401-423) — the Retail Installment Sales Act (RISA) — regulates consumer credit sales of goods where payment is made in installments over time. RISA requires detailed written contracts with specific disclosures: cash price, down payment, APR, total finance charge, payment schedule, security interest details. Buyers have a 3-day right of rescission for home-solicited sales (Personal Property Law § 428). Retailers must provide copies at the time of signing. Failure to comply can void the seller's right to collect finance charges and entitle the buyer to damages. RISA parallels the federal Truth in Lending Act (15 USC 1601 et seq.) but adds NY-specific disclosures and remedies. Does NOT apply to real estate, motor vehicles (separate Motor Vehicle Retail Installment Sales Act), or business transactions."
